Asset Management – Strategy & Product Development
New York, New York, United States
Share with: Facebook
LinkedIn
Twitter
Send to a friend


Two Sigma is a financial technology company in SoHo that explores the fascinating intersection of big data, artificial intelligence, and finance. We currently manage over $40 billion AUM with 1,000+ staff spanning New York, London, Houston, and Hong Kong. We apply the scientific method to investment management and are not your typical investment manager. We follow principles of technology and innovation with equal regard to principles of investment management. Fields like machine learning and distributed computing guide us. Since 2001, we have searched for ways that these kinds of technologies can make us better at what we do.The Strategy & Product Development role is part of the Asset Management Business Development (AMBD) team. AMBD plays an integral role in helping to grow our Asset Management business, which leverages Two Sigma’s research, data, and technology-driven approach to provide investment solutions to leading institutional investors globally. The AMBD group works across teams in modeling / portfolio management, engineering, and investor relations, as well as with colleagues in operational and regulatory-focused areas, to develop and implement our business strategy, cultivate business partnerships, generate and execute on new product ideas, deliver on business expansion initiatives, and drive further operating efficiency for our business. Over just the past few years, AMBD has led the successful launch of dozens of new funds and related investment products for Asset Management’s global institutional investors.The Strategy & Product Development role will focus on designing, evaluating, and launching new investment products. The role will also include identifying and leading projects to improve the firm’s existing investment product offerings. In addition, there will be opportunities to shape and execute on the Asset Management business strategy.QualificationsBachelor’s degree with a strong academic record in finance, economics, mathematics, engineering, or related discipline with a minimum cumulative GPA of 3.56-10 years’ total work experience, with 3+ years’ experience specifically within management consulting, internal strategy and strategic projects, product development, or equivalent; applicable industry and/or investment product experience is a plusSkills and RequirementsOutstanding ability to define and deconstruct problems and intuitively prioritize issuesExcellent analytical / conceptual problem-solving skills with ability to leverage quantitative and qualitative approaches to develop actionable recommendationsDemonstration of high intellectual capacity and curiosity; understanding of financial markets and the investment lifecycle is a plusStrong work ethic (takes ownership), self-starter and quick-study mentality; ability to work independently yet also lead and inspire large cross-functional teamsRobust project management and communication skills with demonstrated ability to gain buy-in from key stakeholdersAdvanced skills in Excel and PowerPoint; coding, database, and SQL experience is a plus 

